article.headline: Denver 69, Troy 61
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Yemi Nicholson had 20 points and a career-high 20 rebounds to lead Denver to a 69-61 victory Saturday night over Troy, the newest member of the Sun Belt Conference. It was the 12th double-double of the year for Nicholson, who had his double-double by halftime. DaShawn Walker added 21 points for the Pioneers (12-9, 5-3 SBC), who have won 16 straight home games. With Troy (10-9, 3-4) trailing 47-42, Bobby Dixon made three straight baskets, including two 3-pointers, to put the Trojans ahead 50-47 for their first lead of the game with 9:53 to go. The Pioneers went on an 8-3 run to lead 55-53 to regain the lead for good with 6:24 left. Dixon finished with 24 points to lead the Trojans. Jarvis Acker had 10 rebounds for Troy.
